The paper deals with the application of deep learning for cardiac auscultation, which involves the interpretation of heart sounds. This falls under the broad category of signal processing and machine learning for healthcare applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Signal Processing), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
